## Adding New Components

When you need a shadcn component that isn't installed yet, use the shadcn CLI:

```bash
# Add a single component
bunx shadcn@latest add <component-name>

# Examples:
bunx shadcn@latest add dialog
bunx shadcn@latest add dropdown-menu
bunx shadcn@latest add tooltip
bunx shadcn@latest add toast
bunx shadcn@latest add data-table

# Add multiple components at once
bunx shadcn@latest add dialog dropdown-menu tooltip
```

The CLI will:
1. Download the component to `src/frontend/components/ui/`
2. Install any required dependencies
3. Configure the component with your project's theme settings

